      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, documented simulation workflow with peer review of setup files is sufficient; formal use-error FMEA is not required.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst within the cardiovascular simulation lab. Mesh, boundary conditions, and solver settings documented in simulation log. No formal FMEA required at MRL 2; level 1 accepted."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, selection of turbulence model and hemolysis power-law with documented literature justification is sufficient; formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating machinery blood flow. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model selected per FDA hemolysis guidance. Literature justification documented. Formal model-form UQ deferred; not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, nominal input values with documented sources (literature, manufacturer data) are sufficient; probabilistic sensitivity analysis is not required.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients taken from published literature with documented sources. Pump geometry from FDA-released CAD file. Nominal values used; sensitivity analysis not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, use of a single well-characterized experimental dataset with documented sample provenance is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark dataset uses bovine blood from a single supplier batch with documented hematocrit and storage conditions. Single dataset accepted at MRL 2; multi-batch statistical characterization not required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, qualitative argument that validation experiment input parameters are representative of the intended COU operating conditions is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark operating conditions (flow rate, RPM, fluid properties) are qualitatively representative of clinical CPB operating envelope. Formal equivalency mapping not required at MRL 2. Qualitative argument documented in validation report section 4.2."
